OL,4,Cof wife and mother
OL,6,FProsecutor Iain Simkin said: "The
OL,7,Fprosecution case is that these two
OL,8,Fmen, the first defendant, Dorothy
OL,9,FMorgan's husband, Robert Morgan, and
OL,10,Fher son by another man, David Holyoak,
OL,11,Fstood by and allowed, watched, as the
OL,12,Fdeceased physically deteriorated in
OL,13,Fher own filth to such a point that
OL,14,Feven though medical assistance was
OL,15,Feventually sought, Dorothy's physical
OL,16,Fwellbeing and clinical condition were
OL,17,Fso bad that, even though she was in
OL,18,Fhospital, her death was an
OL,19,Finevitability."
