OL,4,Cof wife and mother
OL,6,FHe repeatedly claimed that his wife
OL,7,Fhad been refusing medical help to the
OL,8,F999 caller.
OL,10,FBoth Morgan and Holyoak said in
OL,11,Fevidence they were following Mrs
OL,12,FMorgan's wishes that no medical help
OL,13,Fbe sought.
OL,15,FWhen asked by Mr Simkin what
OL,16,Fprovisions there were to ensure Mrs
OL,17,FMorgan was cared for, Holyoak replied:
OL,18,F"I don't remember any", adding "I
OL,19,Fshould have done more."
